# Accessibility (a11y)

Follow WCAG 2.1 AA standards. Use semantic HTML. Test with screen readers and keyboard navigation.

Semantic HTML:

- Use `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation
- Proper heading hierarchy: `<h1>` → `<h2>` → `<h3>`
- Use `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<aside>`, `<section>` landmarks

ARIA attributes:

- `aria-label` for buttons without text
- `aria-describedby` for additional context
- `aria-expanded` for collapsible content
- `role="status"` for live regions

Usage examples:

- `<button aria-label="Close modal" onClick={onClose}><CloseIcon /></button>`
- `<input aria-describedby="email-error" /><div id="email-error">Invalid email</div>`
- `<div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">{errorMessage}</div>`

Keyboard navigation:

- All interactive elements must be focusable
- Implement proper focus management
- Use `tabIndex={-1}` for programmatic focus only
- Provide visible focus indicators

Color and contrast:

- 4.5:1 contrast ratio for normal text
- Don't rely on color alone for information
